  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">I give a self-contained review on radiative <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>⊥</mo></mrow></msub></math> -broadening and radiative energy loss of high-energy partons in QCD matter. The typical <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msubsup><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>⊥</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></math> of high-energy partons receives a double logarithmic correction due to the recoiling effect of medium-induced gluon radiation. Such a double logarithmic term, averaged over the path length of the partons, can be taken as the radiative correction to the jet quenching parameter <math altimg="si3.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mover accent="true"><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow><mrow><mo stretchy="false">ˆ</mo></mrow></mover></math> and hence contributes to radiative energy loss. This has also been confirmed by detailed calculations of energy loss by radiating two gluons.</subfield>
